Operators are used to perform the operations with varaibles and values.
Operators used to control the flow of the program.

=    --> used for assign a value ( assignment operator ) --> var x = 10.

Arthemetoc Operators:
_____________________

1.  + --> to add --> 2+3 = 5
2.  - --> to subtract-->3-2 = 1.
3.  / --> to divison -->35/5 = 6
4.  * --> to multiply ->7*4 = 28

Comparion Operators
___________________
-- used for compare the two values.
-- 
>  --> 2 > 3 ==>  true
<  --> 3 < 2 ==>  True
== --> 1 == 1 =>  True
!= --> 5 != 6 =>  True

Logical Operators:
__________________
-- used to check the conditions.

Ex:
&&  --> AND  --> 1>5 && 5>4  --> False && True ==> False.  --> both condition should be true, to get the true value
||  --> OR   --> 1>5 || 5>4  --> False || True ==> True    --> at least one condition should be true, to get the true value.
!   --> NOT  --> Turns the False value, if the value is return true --> !(2>1)  --> turns to the false

in JS, how to use the Math and Logical Operators
________________________________________________
Maths:
_________
Ex: 
console.log(2+2)      -->4
console.log(1+2+3+4+5) -->15
console.log(10-8)     -->2
console.log(2*3)      -->6
console.log(8/1)      -->8


Logical Operators:
_____________________
console.log(1>2)      -->false
console.log(2>1)      -->true
console.log(1==1)     -->true
